<h2>Book Pickup Service</h2>
<%= @page_title = "Book Pickup & Returns - JH Libraries" %>
<p>
  Starting Monday, June 29, books and materials from the Johns Hopkins Libraries may be requested for pickup on the
  Homewood, East Baltimore, Washington D.C., and Applied Physics Laboratory campuses. At this time, pick up service is available
  for current Johns Hopkins ID cardholders: students, faculty, and staff. Turnaround time for requested books may be longer than
  usual. Only books owned by the Johns Hopkins Libraries are eligible.
</p>
<h3>How to Request Books: </h3>
<ol>
  <li>Log in to <a href="/login">Catalyst</a>, the online catalog, using your JHED credentials.</li>
  <li>Request materials by selecting the “Request Pickup” button indicating your preferred pick up location.</li>
  <li>We will find and prepare the materials for contact-free pick up.</li>
  <li>When your materials are ready, we will notify you by email.
    <span style="font-weight: bold;">If you select MSEL as your pickup location, you will be required to schedule an appointment for pickup. </span>
  </li>
</ol>
<h3>Pick Up Hours & Locations: </h3>
<p>You may pick up materials at any location listed below. Note that APL is restricted to APL staff only.
</p>

<dl class="campus-libraries">
